transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi, I wanted to place an order.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I can help you out. Give me just a moment here.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: What was your first and last name, please?

Speaker 2: Mark Townsend.

Speaker 1: Alrighty, Mr. Townsend. Are you at 475 River Forest Lane, Unit 2320, Talladega?

Speaker 2: Correct, yeah.

Speaker 1: Perfect. So we have an account here for you. It's been a while since you placed any orders.

Speaker 1: What did you want to do today? How many pills did you want to get?

Speaker 1: Did you want to try Viagra? Did you want to get Cialis? What were you thinking?

Speaker 2: I wanted to try the new Viagra.

Speaker 1: Okay, perfect. You wanted to try that new Viagra AGV.

Speaker 2: Alright, give me just a second here. How many pills did you want to do?

Speaker 1: We do 40 for $149, 25 for $99, and for 10 pills, $49.

Speaker 1: So it just depends how many you wanted to get.

Speaker 2: Just wanted to start with the 10, see how it goes.

Speaker 1: Perfect, perfect. And I have confirmed your address already.

Speaker 1: I have an old Discover card here on pilot engine 6188.

Speaker 2: Did you want to use that card today or do you want me to change that for you?

Speaker 1: Yeah, the last numbers were 6188.

Speaker 2: Yep.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's the one I'm using.

Speaker 2: Alright, give me just a moment.

Speaker 1: Alright, Mr. Townsend, so your order has been successfully placed.

Speaker 2: You'll see that process ship out and arrive in the next three to five business days, okay?

Speaker 1: Mm-hmm.

Speaker 2: Alright, then you're all set.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you. Bye now.

Speaker 1: Bye.
